{"id":"227814163_Shortest-Path_Algorithms_Taxonomy_and_Annotation","abstract":"We have evolved a classification scheme to characterize algorithms for solving shortestpath problems. The algorithms are classified according to (A) the problem type, i.e., the question being asked about the given network; (B) the input type, i.e., the salient features of the given network which impact on the design of the algorithm and selection of data structures; and (C) the type of underlying technique employed to solve the problem. An annotated bibliography of 79 selected references on shortest-path algorithms is included. We have also provided a more complete listing of 222 references carefully culled out of a larger body of literature on shortest-path algorithms through the year 1979.","authors":["N. Deo","Chi‚ÄêYin Pang"],"meta":["June 1984Networks 14(2):275 - 323","DOI:10.1002/net.3230140208"],"references":["243097417_Algorithms_for_Obtaining_Shortest_Paths_Visiting_Specified_Nodes","243007324_A_Generalized_Permanent_Label_Setting_Algorithm_for_the_Shortest_Path_Between_Specified_Nodes","323252411_Shortest_Path_in_a_Grid_Network_with_Obstacles","286259742_A_modified_Cascade_algorithm_for_shortest_paths","275164662_Letters_to_the_Editor_Some_Computational_Notes_on_the_Shortest_Route_Problem","268994019_Path-sets_operator_semigroups_and_shortest-path_algorithms_on_a_network","268993855_Shortest_Path_Network_Problems","267674672_All_shortest_routes_in_a_graph","267170000_Computation_of_optimal_paths_in_finite_graphs","267116338_Shortest_distances_through_partitioned_graphs_with_an_application_to_urban_transportation_planning","267079770_Efficient_shortest-route_algorithm","267059668_Bibliography_on_Algorithms_for_Shortest_Path_Shortest_Spanning_Tree_and_Related_Circuit_Routing_Problems_1956-1974","267052456_A_note_on_the_optimality_of_some_all-shortest-path_algorithms","266931923_Calculating_K_th_Shortest_Paths","266925163_On_Some_Communication_Network_Problems","266255871_A_Decompo